  "body": "Hello,\r\nI have a list with items. And I can edit item on a panel that opens above list. \r\nAlso I can edit this item in new tab with SSR.\r\nI use Redux, and I have \"isomorphic\" code.\r\nPanel for item editing is very difficult, and I have composition of several controls. \r\nAnd now I have a task: edit several items simultaneously in one \"window\".\r\n\r\nReact has legacy context: https://reactjs.org/docs/legacy-context.html#how-to-use-context\r\nItemEditPanel receives data from Redux and puts it in Context. Then I can edit two items simultaneously.\r\nBut Context is deprecated. How can this be done without using Context and props proxy?",
